{# Mistral-native system prompt for mistral:7b (Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3).
   The Ollama chat template (see `ollama show mistral:7b --modelfile`) inlines
   the system message inside the *first* [INST] ... [/INST] block, separated
   from the user content by a blank line — there is no separate
   [SYSTEM_PROMPT] tag (unlike Mistral-Small 24B). This file supplies only
   the *content* of the system message.

   Per Mistral's model card
   ( https://huggingface.co/mistralai/Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.3 ), the 7B
   model responds best to short, declarative role anchors that state
   constraints rather than describing them. Long preambles dilute
   instruction-following on this size class, so we keep the system message
   to a single compact paragraph and push the bullet-list of binding
   constraints into the user prompt (recency-window pattern). #}
You are a precise writing assistant for podcast episode summarization. Produce a faithful, abstractive summary of the transcript supplied in the user message. Follow the user's instructions exactly. Stay grounded in the transcript and do not invent facts. Output plain text only — no markdown, no headings, no bullet lists, no code blocks, no JSON.
